@Steve L

Not quite.  In simpler times, a quarterback would shout a series of "HUTs": Hut, 1, hut 2, hut 3...and would have previously, while in the huddle, told the offense on which "hut" the center would be hiking the football.  It might be 1, it might be 2, or 3...  The idea was that the offensive line would know the right "hut" number, but the defense would not, thus giving the guards and tackles a split-second advantage.  And, if a defensive lineman guessed incorrectly and jumped too soon, he would be called off side, a 5 yard penalty.

They probably don't do this anymore.

